Borrowed from {{bor|en|ML.|ultrāmarīnus}}, from {{der|en|la|ultrā|t=beyond}} + {{m|la|marīnus|t=of or relating to the sea, marine}}. {{m|la||Ultrā}} is derived from {{m|la|uls|t=beyond}} (from {{der|en|ine-pro|*h₂el-|t=beyond; other}}) + {{m|la|-ter|pos={{glossary|suffix}} forming {{glossary|adverb}}s}} + {{m|la|-ā|pos=suffix forming adverbs}}; while {{m|la||marīnus}} is from {{m|la|mare|t=sea}} (ultimately from {{der|en|ine-pro|*mer-|t=sea; lake; wetland}}) + {{m|la|-īnus|pos=suffix meaning ‘of or pertaining to’ forming adjectives}}.<ref name="OED">{{R:OED Online|pos=adj.'' and ''n|id=208702|date=March 2021|nodot=1}}; {{R:Lexico|pos=n}}</ref> The English word is analysable as {{prefix|en|ultra|marine}}.

{{glossary|Noun}} sense 1 (“pigment”) refers to the fact that lapis lazuli was obtained from foreign countries and hence “beyond the sea”.<ref name="OED"/>

